<body>

<!-- Main container for the demo -->
<div id="demo-container">

    <!-- Title and Description -->
    <h1>Wankel Rotary Engine: Epitrochoidal Envelopes</h1>
    <p>This Demonstration gives an animation of an epitrochoid and associated planetary-motion envelope curve. The configuration shown has applications in the internal combustion engines invented by Felix Wankel and popularized by Mazda in RX-7 and RX-8 cars. The "eccentricity ratio" changes the shapes of the curves. The "reference frame" determines what is held stationary in the animation: either the epitrochoid (blue), the envelope curve (orange), or the centers of rotation of both curves. The "inner" envelope is the triangular rotor shape used in a Wankel rotary engine, whereas the "outer" envelope is the continuation of the envelope curve along the opposite extreme of motion.</p>

    <!-- Control Panel -->
    <div id="control-panel">
        <div>
            <label for="slider-eccentricity">eccentricity ratio</label>
